introduction: Cedrus, with the common English name cedar, is a genus of coniferous trees in the plant family Pinaceae (subfamily Abietoideae). They are native to the mountains of the western Himalayas and the Mediterranean region, occurring at altitudes of 1,5003,200 m (4,90010,500 ft) in the Himalayas and 1,0002,200 m (3,3007,200 ft) in the Mediterranean.[1]
